import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In[23]:
# Utility Functions
def show(img, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

def apply_kernel(img, kernel):
    return cv2.filter2D(img.astype(np.float32), -1, kernel)
In[29]:
# 1. Traffic Signs - Sobel
traffic = cv2.imread(r'image.png', cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)

# Display original image it should not only in blue tint
show(traffic, "Original Traffic Signs Image")



# make the image grayscale
traffic = cv2.cvtColor(traffic, cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)

# Built-in Sobel
sobelx = cv2.Sobel(traffic, cv2.CV_64F, 1, 0, ksize=3)
sobely = cv2.Sobel(traffic, cv2.CV_64F, 0, 1, ksize=3)
sobel_combined = cv2.magnitude(sobelx, sobely)
show(np.uint8(np.absolute(sobelx)), "Sobel Built-in - Horizontal")
show(np.uint8(np.absolute(sobely)), "Sobel Built-in - Vertical")
show(np.uint8(sobel_combined), "Sobel Built-in - Both")

# User-defined Sobel
sobel_kx = np.array([[-1,0,1],[-2,0,2],[-1,0,1]])
sobel_ky = np.array([[1,2,1],[0,0,0],[-1,-2,-1]])
gx = apply_kernel(traffic, sobel_kx)
gy = apply_kernel(traffic, sobel_ky)
sobel_user = np.hypot(gx, gy)
show(np.uint8(np.abs(gx)), "Sobel User - Horizontal")
show(np.uint8(np.abs(gy)), "Sobel User - Vertical")
show(np.uint8(sobel_user), "Sobel User - Both")

# 2. X-Ray Bones - Prewitt 
xray = cv2.imread('bone_xray.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

# Display original image
show(xray, "Original X-Ray Image")

# Built-in (Simulated)
prewitt_kx = np.array([[-1,0,1],[-1,0,1],[-1,0,1]])
prewitt_ky = np.array([[1,1,1],[0,0,0],[-1,-1,-1]])
px = apply_kernel(xray, prewitt_kx)
py = apply_kernel(xray, prewitt_ky)
p_mag = np.hypot(px, py)
show(np.uint8(np.abs(px)), "Prewitt Built-in - Horizontal")
show(np.uint8(np.abs(py)), "Prewitt Built-in - Vertical")
show(np.uint8(p_mag), "Prewitt Built-in - Both")

# User-defined Prewitt
gx_p = apply_kernel(xray, prewitt_kx)
gy_p = apply_kernel(xray, prewitt_ky)
mag_p = np.hypot(gx_p, gy_p)
show(np.uint8(np.abs(gx_p)), "Prewitt User - Horizontal")
show(np.uint8(np.abs(gy_p)), "Prewitt User - Vertical")
show(np.uint8(mag_p), "Prewitt User - Both")

print("Prewitt vs Sobel: Prewitt is simpler and more sensitive to noise, Sobel gives smoother edges.")

Prewitt vs Sobel: Prewitt is simpler and more sensitive to noise, Sobel gives smoother edges.
In[31]:
# ---------- 3. Satellite Image - Roberts ----------
satellite = cv2.imread('satellite_lowres.jpeg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

# Display original image
show(satellite, "Original Satellite Image")

# Built-in (Simulated)
roberts_kx = np.array([[1,0],[0,-1]])
roberts_ky = np.array([[0,1],[-1,0]])
rx = apply_kernel(satellite, roberts_kx)
ry = apply_kernel(satellite, roberts_ky)
r_mag = np.hypot(rx, ry)
show(np.uint8(np.abs(rx)), "Roberts Built-in - Gx")
show(np.uint8(np.abs(ry)), "Roberts Built-in - Gy")
show(np.uint8(r_mag), "Roberts Built-in - Both")

# User-defined Roberts
gx_r = apply_kernel(satellite, roberts_kx)
gy_r = apply_kernel(satellite, roberts_ky)
mag_r = np.hypot(gx_r, gy_r)
show(np.uint8(np.abs(gx_r)), "Roberts User - Gx")
show(np.uint8(np.abs(gy_r)), "Roberts User - Gy")
show(np.uint8(mag_r), "Roberts User - Both")

print("Roberts Limitations: 2x2 kernel sensitive to noise, not ideal for complex real-world images.")

Roberts Limitations: 2x2 kernel sensitive to noise, not ideal for complex real-world images.

surv = cv2.imread('surveillance.jpeg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

# Display original image

show(np.uint8(np.absolute(lap)), "Laplacian - Directionless Edge Detection")

#  5. MRI - Canny
mri = cv2.imread('mri_brain.jpeg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

# Display original image
show(mri, "Original MRI Image")

# Built-in Canny
canny_b = cv2.Canny(mri, 50, 150)
show(canny_b, "Canny Built-in")

# User-defined Canny
def canny_user(img):
    blur = cv2.GaussianBlur(img, (5,5), 1.4)
    gx = cv2.Sobel(blur, cv2.CV_64F, 1, 0, ksize=3)
    gy = cv2.Sobel(blur, cv2.CV_64F, 0, 1, ksize=3)
    mag = cv2.magnitude(gx, gy)
    mag = np.uint8(mag / mag.max() * 255)
    return cv2.Canny(mag, 50, 150)

canny_u = canny_user(mri)
show(canny_u, "Canny User-defined")

print("""Canny Multi-step Advantage:
1. Gaussian smoothing reduces noise.
2. Gradient computation finds edges accurately.
3. Non-maximum suppression thins edges.
4. Double threshold & hysteresis connect real edges, reduce false ones.""")

Canny Multi-step Advantage:
1. Gaussian smoothing reduces noise.
2. Gradient computation finds edges accurately.
3. Non-maximum suppression thins edges.
4. Double threshold & hysteresis connect real edges, reduce false ones.
